The Telegraph - Calcutta : Sports

 ACC vows to back Pawar

OUR SPECIAL CORRESPONDENT

Calcutta: The Asian Cricket Council (ACC) has vowed afresh to back the Board of Control for Cricket in India chief, Sharad Pawar, in his drive to become the next president of the world body the International Cricket Council (ICC). 

According to The Telegraphs sources, members of the ACCs executive board took that vow during a meeting in Bangkok on Saturday. 

Besides the four Full (Test) Members, seven from the ACC are Associate Members of the world body. 

Pawar and Englands David Morgan are locked in battle to succeed Percy Sonn who, at the moment, remains critical in the intensive care unit of a Cape Town hospital. 

The ICC chief developed complications after colon surgery. 




